<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="D" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Despair2" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Despair,</orth> vb. to be without hope, to despond: <bibl n="shak. luc 1447" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 1447</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. son 140.9" default="NO" valid="yes">Sonn. 140, 9</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tgv 3.1.247" default="NO" valid="yes">Gentl. III, 1, 247</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. shr 3.1.45" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. III, 1, 45</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. aww 4.3.86" default="NO" valid="yes">All's IV, 3, 86</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wt 1.2.198" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. I, 2, 198</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jn 4.3.126" default="NO" valid="yes">John IV, 3, 126</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r2 2.2.67" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 II, 2, 67</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r2 2.2.67" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 II, 2, 67</bibl> <bibl n="shak. 3h6 1.1.178" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C I, 1, 178</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 1.2.86" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 I, 2, 86</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 5.3.120" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 3, 120</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 5.3.120" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 3, 120</bibl> <bibl n="shak. tit 2.1.91" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. II, 1, 91</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. rom 1.1.228" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. I, 1, 228</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cym 5.5.61" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. V, 5, 61</bibl>. Followed by <cit><quote>of:</quote> <bibl n="shak. luc 983" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 983</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 2.1.17" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A II, 1, 17</bibl>.<lb />Transitively: <cit><quote>d. thy charm,</quote> <bibl n="shak. mac 5.8.13" default="NO" valid="yes">Mcb. V, 8, 13</bibl></cit> (or is it == may thy charm despair?).
